s_somewhat + nature_intrinsic_value + climate_tipping_points + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 10 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWW1z0zoa%2FSvPMMtu0tukjvNetjtT%2BnJhKNApZZk7lAmKrSTa2pZXshsCF377Hkl24tBwMdsvHde2znOeVx0rXx6FfMbyKDuRIX90%2BOjggI6OjuhaMZFQJilQ7PMKF8uEbnLf6%2FRoKVUU3gm%2BpGVn4k%2B6k96kPxlORpOORw2dyZQ6XtOA3CQAO9Y6j9NMyISCBTAPyaOUKRksBIsMZGfsU4dmTE3Ykq0mizxmiS4f%2BMQSEbNIT7SM%2BXLBsvJJlxKW5YpPRJIpkWgRTO5YlPPyeY%2BCCCszPslEmopkPkklXl0j92mW2%2FXO4ASvZlxNliJbTEKhA5knGVaVrw%2FXRIoX2SSSazIj0vlsxpUxM5NBrnm4ds2jhGeThM9ZJu74xMFMIlxrG6AzFiyIbaIkNDG6XGULXM9ExAl52DzWB5SZKLAw1PukOJInEq5JKgumeAvBZTEHRaFxP1twF%2Fd%2FaDicBBbjCQUyTqU2%2Fq1fwNok5EDELeGo6YwlIYtkwilGdURt%2BrhO%2FtndR0PVLOefUh5kWOgSIGcWYVMnbQv2lOuMpvmKcmPGLNS86tghvVkoEaf0jkeoBk6XSv4HuG7172evzq6Or89OabqiOU%2B4Qmrb6aosSh6KbCtMe3i4TwlyZMmYSALJYr1NAq4y43IsFYpwHTHt3nXhYGkaCa7b9GYVtyM5T6RC4hpf0v4%2BpeP%2B16bFstkae4%2Fp5PkT%2B%2BaUZ8zdTZWcsqmIRAYiU2ncDk1Hvff2qfOhTec