imals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 nature_intrinsic_value → 4 climate_tipping_points → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 10 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWGtv2zgW%2FSsXwXbXzvghyW93s0CaONOiSRukGQSDpnBpibY5kUgtScV1O%2B1v30tSsuVY3RrIl0SWyHPPfV%2Fy21FE5ySL9ZmI6NH4qN2Gk5MTuJWEcdACQkm%2BrvFhxeE%2BCzy%2FCysh4%2BiR0RWs%2FGkw7Uy70950MPU9qCktUvC9uoG45wh1qlSWpJoJDuESEcfgQUqkCJeMxAbQHwXgw5zIKVmR9XSZJYSr4kMAhLOExGqqREJXS6KLLx3gRGeSThnXknHFwukjiTNafO9CGONOTaeapSnji2kqcOkGuQfzzO53Aqe4VFM5XTG9nEZMhSLjGncVywcbIvlCMo3Fhgxqzqmecrogmj3SqVs7jfFZWStMSLgEsjUFU0Dgeq2X%2BDxnMQU09fazaoM2qpIoUg2QFP3DOFUgpAWTtIkWJAlFHkzhe72kzrj%2FUqgVDy3GSwhFkgpllNgswL08ooiIr5ijpjThEYkFp5BgAMQt%2BLzx7%2BTxs6FqttMvKQ01bnRWFnOLsA2FlgV7RZWGWbaGzIgxGxUtKzaGD0vJkhTuaIwup3AtxV%2BI63b%2FPnk3uTm9nZzDbA0LyqlE%2F7XSdRF3NGJ6x0zH%2BLEBHB1hyRhLIpLF%2BoOHVGqjciIkRtrGYsqtdeYgaRozqlrwYZ20YrHgQqLjat%2FSXgPSUe973WJZb428F3D25qVdOaOauLepFDMyYzHTSGQmjNqRSZqPXgP8Ty24IKEWKBN1dVC4IDU%2B4LoBSgA1gSHkAj03%2Bbg6P738s%2F2PTzCjsVhhTpi91sP0Cz7Ha9yO2GhVi4WyoyzUzhfoPYpxjOq7vLhDn66vqXyN1jWGPtlXEVOx5flW0TEE3%2BsACGo5NOl%2FM4aORpaQoh%2BXOQhK1DYKxmh03kyIfKAayTGlKdq76WKjDXe31zAXuA9NowlqGgr%2BiO5wtrEioBZKoVQzROwHfI8el%2FSRoswIKH9kUvAExZO4mYhHah5BkVCyOQspegXRMdRuXWqfiRkGyxyDo1LLQsVurmJeGJBUs9iHabjRDbQ